						               													<description>The greedy troll has stolen the dwarves' treasure and taken it to his mountain. He knows that the dwarves want to get it back. That's why he runs back and forth between his kingdom and the dwarves' kingdom to catch the dwarves. If he succeeds, the treasure will be his forever and he will have won. Fortunately, the dwarves have the support of Aquarius and Fairy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is suitable for children from three years and has the peculiarity that the group of players together wins or loses against the troll. The players do not compete against each other. Especially for children who are just starting with board games and are still learning to endure the frustration of losing, this game is an enrichment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game Troll dich! combines ideas and design of our children's book author and illustrator Kristin Franke with the traditional craft of Erzgebirge folk art. The figures are hand-turned and made by toy maker Tino G&amp;uuml;nther, the famous inventor of the virologist incense man.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
